              <a href="/admissions/contact" class="nav-link">Contact Us</a>
              <span class="nav-link separator">External Links</span>
              <a href="http://www.birmingham.ac.uk/undergraduate/fees/index.aspx" class="nav-link">Undergraduate Fees &amp; Finance</a>
              <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/UoBCSUGApplicants2018/" class="nav-link">UG Facebook Group</a>
            </div>
          </nav>
          <p>We offer a number of the following Scholarship for UK/EU applicants:</p>

<p><strong>£3000 for the first year of study</strong>:  In order to be eligible for consideration of our £3000 Scholarship, applicants must hold an offer, have attended an Applicant Visit Day and made Birmingham their Firm choice by 1st August.  The Scholarship Committee will meet in mid-August to review all suitable applications, and decisions will be made on content of application and final grades achieved.  Successful applicants will be notified via email/post.</p>

<p>Alternative arrangements will be made for EU students not resident in the UK. (These applicants will be contacted directly regarding these arrangements.)</p>

<p><strong>Please note that there are only a limited number of scholarships available, and these are awarded to the students with the best entrance exam results</strong>.</p>

<hr />

<p><strong><em>Applicants applying for the <a href="https://www.cs.bham.ac.uk/admissions/undergraduate/degrees/cspwc">BSc Computer Science with Digital Technology Partnership degree</a> are not eligible for the department scholarship.</em></strong></p>

